  "prompt": "Why do girls wear sports bras?",
  "response": "Girls and women wear sports bras for several reasons:\n\n1. **Support and Comfort:** Sports bras are designed to provide support to the breasts during physical activities. They help minimize movement and reduce discomfort, pain, or potential injury.\n\n2. **Improved Performance:** By reducing breast movement, sports bras allow girls to focus better on their activities and perform without distraction or discomfort.\n\n3. **Protection:** Sports bras can help prevent damage to breast tissue, which can occur due to excessive movement and bouncing during exercise.\n\n4. **Coverage:** Sports bras offer additional coverage, which can make girls feel more comfortable and confident during activities.\n\n5. **Moisture Management:** Many sports bras are made from material that wicks away sweat, helping to keep the wearer dry and comfortable.\n\n6. **Versatility:** Sports bras are often designed to be worn both during workouts and as everyday wear due to their comfort and supportive features.\n\nOverall, sports bras are a practical and essential piece of athletic wear for girls engaging in physical activities.",
